transcript.text: Hello, welcome back to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In today's video, we will learn to create a PDF block path in Adobe Illustrator.
Creating a block path in Adobe Illustrator typically involves creating a shape or path that appears as a solid block of color without any visible stroke or outline.
Here's how you can do it.
Open your file in Adobe Illustrator.
Select the pen tool to draw a path.
Now create a path with your preferred shape.
Copy the path and paste it into a new document.
You can use the shortcut Control plus N to open a new document and Control plus we to paste the path into the new document.
Next, select the artboard tool to resize the page according to the path size.
Now navigate to the preset menu and select Fit to selected art.
Select the path and save it as an SVG format.
Select SVG from the drop down menu.
Once done, click on the save button.
Finally, check the settings for SVG format.
Save the file in PDF format by selecting PDF from the drop down menu and then clicking on the save button.
Your document will be saved on the desktop.
Open the document using Edit with Notepad++.
Copy this path to paste it into the Custom Properties window.
In the PDF Block plugin, open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat.
Click on the PDF Lib Blocks menu to activate the PDF Lib Block tool.
Draw one block using the PDF Lib Block plugin.

While drawing this block, consider the below points #1 the block should cover the highest left of the path #2 block should cover the highest right of the path #3 block should cover the highest bottom of the path #4 block should cover the highest top of the path.
Match the right, left, bottom, and top sides perfectly with the borders of the path.
Select the type of block.
For example, you can choose the image block.
Set block properties using the property window.
Set the fit method and position from this properties window.
You can add the default image here.
In addition, you can add custom properties using this window.
Since this is an image block, you need to set this block at the highest of four sides.
Now the PDF file is ready for upload.
Save the file from the File menu.
Add a clip path to the image block using Manage Properties and you have successfully created the block PDF path in the Illustrator tool.
Hope you enjoyed the video.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
